race.comment: MONTE TREMEZZO (9) turned in a good figure last start despite getting beaten by 0.6L. This is a tougher race, but she's proven to be right up to this grade and Fiore reunites with the filly. Maps beautifully, she'll be at her peak now and she looks poised to strike in this suitable race. HEY PINO (2) was solid last start at Ascot when 2.5L off the winner in Saturday grade. Back to this level is a good move and he strikes a winnable race with Faithfull on board. Racing well this campaign and can continue his strong run of form. HISTORY WON'T CARE (3) hasn't been sighted since his last start back in August where he disappointed on a wet deck. He boasts a strong fresh record however and Pike has been booked. No trial coming in is the query, though there's enough there to suggest he can return on a positive note. LENIENCY (1) is building nicely this time in work and is not to be discounted.
